7.  Hanging  Cylinder.  [10  points] 


A  cylinder  of  mass  M  and  radius  R  is  suspended  at  one  side  by  a  length  of  rope,  while 
the  other  side  rests  against  a  vertical  wall.  The  coeﬃcient  of  friction  between  the  wall  and 
cylinder  surfaces  is  µ.  The  rope  extends  oﬀ  at  an  angle  θ  relative  to  the  vertical  wall.  The 
whole  system  remains  at  rest.  Constant  gravity  acts  downward. 

What  is  the  minimum  angle  θ  for  which  this  setup  remains  stationary?  Explain  why  this  is 
a  minimum  angle  and  not  a  maximum  angle  (i.e.,  explain  what  happens  if  the  ball  is  placed 
higher  or  lower  on  the  wall). 

